  <titleInfo>
    <title>1844 Jun. 8, Carthage [Tennessee, to unknown recipient] / [Adam Fergusson]</title>
  </titleInfo>
  <abstract>This is a letter to an unknown recipient dated June 8, 1844. The author is most likely Adam Fergusson. Fergusson is writing to announce the nomination of James K. Polk for president. He describes the convention party in Carthage. According to Fergusson the citizens celebrated with great enthusiasm. Fergusson also writes about people's reactions to the nomination.</abstract>
